-- Barclays Hires Paul Knight, Phillip Huang From UBS, Vlaad Says
-- B y   K a t i a   D m i t r i e v a
-- 2013-08-30T16:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-30/barclays-hires-paul-knight-phillip-huang-from-ubs-vlaad-says.html
Richard Kim moved to  National Bank
of Canada (NA)  as an infrastructure analyst from Macquarie Capital
Markets, according to Vlaad & Co., a Toronto-based financial
services recruiting firm.  Other moves noted in the “Bill’s Buzz” weekly  newsletter 
include:  *  Barclays Plc (BARC)  added Paul Knight as vice chairman and co-head of
global metals and mining from UBS AG, where he was chief
exective officer of the Canadian unit. The firm also added
Phillip Huang, a telecom equity research analyst from UBS.  * James Kisil left Toronto-Dominion Bank, where he was an
investment banking associate, and joined Ontario Public Service
Employees Union as an associate portfolio manager in the private
markets group.  * Desjardins Securities added Leslie Yang as an analyst in
 investment banking  from the Bank of Montreal.  To contact the reporter on this story:
